nl.vpro.couchdb

Class CouchdbOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.vpro.couchdb.CouchdbOptions

  • public class CouchdbOptions
extends Object
    Used to pass query CouchdbOptions to view queries. For example: 
     database.queryView("company/all", Map.class,
     new CouchdbOptions().count(1).descending(true));

    In contrast to earlier versions of this class it became clear that some CouchdbOptions needs to be JSON encoded and some CouchdbOptions musn't be JSON encoded. There is no way around that, that's just the way CouchDB works.

    Internally, this class keeps a list of CouchdbOptions that need JSON encoding:

    • key
    • startkey
    • endkey

    It will automatically encode those option names. If you need to have non-supported CouchdbOptions encoded you have to subclass CouchdbOptions and then access putEncoded(String, Object).

    Author:
    Michiel Meeuwissen (copied from org.jcouchdb.db.Options with reduced dependencies)
